This was fun when I was 13, eight years ago. Messed around with it again - it hasn't improved much. This app is cool for the novelty, but the sound quality is obviously lacking once you put on some studio-quality headphones. Best for quick drum beats; kinda painful otherwise. The FX need major fixing. The distortion especially does not have a good sound whatsoever (I promise I know how to use it), and the 'filter' pans the sound left (???). Severely lacking a compressor or limiter.

I make hip hop and digital r&b with this app. There is too much sampling goin on the music world today. All you really need is a few instruments. The app is perfect and the fx and oscillators give you a variety of different tones. Low bass, phased out melodies, distorted riffs, and the boom 808 drums. Im a producer and I cosign RD4 groovebox.

This app is my favorite for acid it's just much faster than anything else

one am glad to see something that has its own character. I can't stress 
enough how quickly ideas come out in this program. I was quite pleased to 
read in the description something I have long suspected, this is indeed the 
grandbaby of the legendary Rubber Duck! I just want to know when RD5 is 
coming? Would be way cool to have more kits and more velocity steps for the 
drum sequencer, and possibly some kind of pad generator, this is one of the 
most creative and FUN apps around I'd hate to see it die. Truly, it's the 
only app I absolutely must have on my phone, that's saying a lot since I 
have purchased quite a few of them.

Gets better with every update. Quality sound and great fun. I'm making tunes that sound the same as the 12" vinyl I used to buy in the early 90's! Very cool. Needs more though: a 3rd synth (and not just another bassline machine) and a song building mode. Caustic 2 is the best though.

Just a few things are missing like recording parameter changes, song mode where you record custom pattern changes (you can only cycle through all patterns today)  and a few more tweaker knobs for the drum machine and we'll be in heaven!  It already has a WAV output mode where you can go knb crazy so the authors are slowly getting around to getting this to a state of usability to rival what we have on the PC.

Could of pressed the refund button a little quicker because the audio engine is always tearing after a few minutes but the app in general is adequate. It's also missing a few options like adding samples to the drum machine ala Electrum (I guess to encourage you to buy SPC) and effects rack is a joke compared to what Beatmaker or even Rebirth on the iPhone had 2-3 yrs ago. P.S: You pretty much need to buy the SPC Drum app (Which is a better initial investment but also still lacking in certain avenues) for this app to find any value past a twenty minute distraction.

It may not have the most features of the grooveboxes available on android, but this is probably the most intuitive, and definitely the easiest to play on the fly. Caustic and uloops feel more like compositions tools, RD3 feels more like an instrument, which is the most important feature in my book.
